-- Legal & General says board member Pollock to retire May 2015
-- By Carolyn Cohn
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 04:35AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 16 (Reuters) - Life insurance and pensions company Legal & General <LGEN.L> said on Tuesday that its board member responsible for the firm's protections and savings business would retire.

John Pollock, executive director and CEO of the Legal & General Assurance Society, plans to retire at the firm's next annual general meeting in May 2015, L&G said in a statement. [ID:nRSP7220Ra] The protections and savings business provided over 6 million individual customers and over 8,000 corporate schemes with life insurance, general insurance and savings plans, producing an operating profit of 444 million pounds ($718.04 million) in 2013 and "a strong performance" in the first half of 2014, the company said.